### REST replication. The FXService has no CDS model — the consumption
### entity declares its shape locally and points at a plain HTTP endpoint:
###
###   @federation.replicate: {
###       source: 'FXService',
###       delta: { field: 'modifiedAt' },
###       rest: {
###           path: '/api/rates',
###           pagination: { type: 'offset', pageSize: 100 },
###           deltaParam: 'modifiedSince',
###           dataPath: 'results'
###       }
###   }
###
### The REST adapter pages through the endpoint via `limit`/`offset`, then
### the pipeline UPSERTs each row into the local `ExchangeRates` table.

### Full sync
POST http://localhost:4005/pipeline/run
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"ExchangeRates","mode":"full"}

### Query replicated rates locally — orderable, filterable, countable
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/ExchangeRates?$filter=quoteCurrency eq 'USD'&$orderby=rateDate

### Delta sync — only rows with modifiedAt > lastSync on the tracker
POST http://localhost:4005/pipeline/run
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"ExchangeRates","mode":"delta"}

### Idempotency check — same run twice, same row count
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/ExchangeRates?$count=true&$top=0
